class Solution {
    public int distanceTraveled(int mainTank, int additionalTank) {
        int distance = 0;
        while (mainTank > 0 || additionalTank > 0) {
            int fuelConsumed = Math.min(5, mainTank);
            distance += fuelConsumed * 10;
            mainTank -= fuelConsumed;
            if (mainTank < 5 && additionalTank > 0) {
                mainTank += 1;
                additionalTank -= 1;
            }
        }
        return distance;
    }
}
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n), where n is the number of iterations until the main tank and additional tank are empty
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW

